decks.notes: The main focus of this deck is to control the game through Counterspells, bounce effects, and card selection. With Octavia, Living Thesis as the commander, the deck aims to disrupt the opponent's game plan and protect its own win conditions. The deck includes a wide range of cheap counter spells like Counterspell, Force of Will, and Force Spike to prevent the opponent from resolving key spells. Bounce effects like Boomerang and Chain of Vapor help to deal with troublesome permanents on the battlefield. The deck also includes card selection spells like Ponder, Preordain, and Brainstorm to ensure a smooth draw and consistently find the right answers to control the game. Overall, the deck seeks to outmaneuver opponents and dominate the game through control strategies.

The main concept of this deck is to control the game through ramping and land manipulation while setting up powerful threats like Emrakul and Primeval Titan. Azusa, Lost But Seeking allows for explosive plays by playing multiple lands each turn, taking advantage of cards like Exploration and Burgeoning to accelerate mana production. The deck aims to disrupt opponents with cards like Oblivion Stone and Maze of Ith, while also utilizing cards like Crucible of Worlds and Ramunap Excavator to recur lands and maintain board presence. By utilizing a combination of ramp, control elements, and powerful threats, this deck seeks to outvalue and outmaneuver opponents in a Duel Commander 1 vs 1 format.

The main theme of this deck revolves around utilizing various methods of graveyard recursion and combo pieces in order to generate a powerful win condition. By combining cards that allow for reanimation, discard, and sacrifice effects, the deck aims to quickly assemble a lethal combo that can overwhelm the opponent and secure victory. The deck also includes a mix of disruption and removal spells to help control the board and protect its combo pieces. Overall, the strategy of this deck is to carefully plan out its moves, setting up the necessary pieces before unleashing a devastating combo that can quickly close out the game.
